    <h2><span class=3D"cmp-richtext--fz-h5 cmp-richtext--ff-mark cmp-richte=
xt--fw-regular"><span class=3D"cmp-richtext--fz-h3 cmp-richtext--ff-mark cm=
p-richtext--fw-heavy">Points to know</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li>When an investment increases in value, the increase is considered a cap=
ital gain.</li>
<li>Capital gains are "realized" (and subject to tax) when you sell the inv=
estment.</li>
<li>Capital gains are subject to different tax rates depending on how long =
you owned the investment.</li>
<li>Strategies that can help minimize capital gains taxes include tax-loss =
harvesting, holding investments for over a year, using tax-advantaged accou=
nts, and making charitable donations.</li>
</ul>

</div>

   =20

</div>
<div class=3D"richtext text cmp-richtext--large-spacing aem-GridColumn aem-=
