<div data-cmp-data-layer=3D"{&quot;richtext-4163c77de6&quot;:{&quot;@type&q=
uot;:&quot;vanguard-retail-common/components/richtext/v1/richtext&quot;,&qu=
ot;repo:modifyDate&quot;:&quot;2025-01-28T14:13:02Z&quot;,&quot;xdm:text&qu=
ot;:&quot;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span class=3D\&quot;cmp-richtext--fz-h3 cmp-richtex=
t--ff-mark cmp-richtext--fw-heavy\&quot;&gt;What are capital gains taxes?&l=
t;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Capital gains are profits on an investme=
nt. When you sell investments at a higher price than what you paid for them=
, the capital gains are &amp;quot;realized.&amp;quot; You'll owe taxes on y=
our realized gains. Investments subject to capital gains taxes include stoc=
ks, bonds, mutual funds, real estate, and valuable personal property like a=
rtwork, jewelry, and collectibles.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Figuring=
 out how much of your sale amount was made up of taxable &lt;a href=3D\&quo=
t;#modal-earnings\&quot;&gt;earnings&lt;/a&gt; can be tricky. You'll first =
need to know how much you originally paid for the &lt;a href=3D\&quot;#moda=
l-shares\&quot;&gt;shares&lt;/a&gt; (your cost basis).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&g=
t;&lt;a href=3D\&quot;/content/retail/public/us/en/investor-resources-educa=
tion/taxes/cost-basis.html\&quot;&gt;Learn more about cost basis&lt;/a&gt;&=
lt;/p&gt;\r\n&quot;}}" id=3D"richtext-4163c77de6" class=3D"cmp-richtext ">
    <h2><span class=3D"cmp-richtext--fz-h3 cmp-richtext--ff-mark cmp-richte=
xt--fw-heavy">What are capital gains taxes?</span></h2>
<p>Capital gains are profits on an investment. When you sell investments at=
 a higher price than what you paid for them, the capital gains are "realize=
d." You'll owe taxes on your realized gains. Investments subject to capital=
 gains taxes include stocks, bonds, mutual funds, real estate, and valuable=
 personal property like artwork, jewelry, and collectibles.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Figuring out how much of your sale amount was made up of taxable <a href=
=3D"https://investor.vanguard.com/investor-resources-education/taxes/realiz=
ed-capital-gains#modal-earnings" data-initialized=3D"true">earnings</a> can=
 be tricky. You'll first need to know how much you originally paid for the =
<a href=3D"https://investor.vanguard.com/investor-resources-education/taxes=
/realized-capital-gains#modal-shares" data-initialized=3D"true">shares</a> =
(your cost basis).</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://investor.vanguard.com/investor-resources-education/ta=
xes/cost-basis">Learn more about cost basis</a></p>

</div>

   =20

</div>
