xt--fw-heavy">Primary residence exclusion</span></h3>
<p>If you decide to sell a property that you've lived in for at least 2 of =
the past 5 years, you may be able to exclude up to $250,000 if you file ind=
ividually or $500,000 if you file jointly. That means that if the profit is=
 under these limits, you won't owe any capital gains tax.</p>
<p>On the other hand, for investment properties, the entire profit from the=
 sale is subject to capital gains tax. The exact amount of tax owed will de=
pend on the length of time the property was owned and the individual's inco=
me.</p>

